New Records: Kumar Rocker tied Don Stanhouse for second-most strikeouts in club history over their first two MLB appearances with 12 strikeouts, behind David Clyde's 14 strikeouts in 1973.
Key Match Events: Kumar Rocker struck out five batters in his home debut at Globe Life Field.
Rocker allowed two runs (one earned) on two hits and four walks over three innings.
Rocker struck out Davis Schneider on three pitches, including an 85.2 mph slider.
Rocker struck out Joey Loperfido on three pitches, including an 85 mph slider.
Nathan Lukes scored a run with a sacrifice fly to left.
Rocker struck out Ernie Clement on a check swing on a 95 mph sinker.
Rocker struck out Loperfido on three pitches, including looking on an 83.4 mph slider.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Kumar Rocker had Tommy John surgery in May 2023 after being the No. 3 overall pick in the 2022 MLB Draft.
